</div>

<div class="home-summary">
    <h2>About This Text</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>Panchikaran</strong> is a foundational Advaita Vedānta treatise by <strong>Adi Shankaracharya</strong>
        that explains how the five subtle elements (Tanmatras) undergo a fivefold combination (Panchikaran) to produce
        the gross elements of the physical universe — and how understanding this process reveals the identity of the
        individual Self (Jiva) with Brahman.
    </p>
    <p>
        This edition — <em>Sartha Satik Panchikaran</em> — is a Marathi translation and detailed commentary,
        making the Sanskrit text accessible with thorough explanations, illustrative analogies (Dṛṣṭānta),
        and systematic tables (Koshtaka) to guide the sincere student of Vedānta.
    </p>

